    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        static MessageDigest getInstance​(String algorithm)
                          throws NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                                 NoSuchProviderException
        Retrieves an instance of the desired message digest algorithm, if available. By default will prefer a GPU enabled implementation over a CPU enabled implementation. Will fall back on a CPU implementation in the absence of an available GPU implementation or supported GPU acceleration card.
        Parameters:
        algorithm - the identifier for the requested algorithm
        Returns:
        a MessageDigest implementation for the requested algorithm
        Throws:
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - if there are no available or supported implementations for the requested algorithm
        NoSuchProviderException - if there are no registered providers that can support the requested algorithm

      • compute

        void compute​(Message message)
        Computes a cryptographic hash (message digest) for the given message. The resulting hash value will be returned by the Message.getHash() method once the future (accessible from Message.getFuture()) has been completed.
        Parameters:
        message - the message to be hashed

      • computeAsync

        static void computeAsync​(Message... messages)
        Computes a cryptographic hash (message digest) for the given array of messages. The resulting hash value will be returned by the Message.getHash() method once the future (accessible from Message.getFuture()) has been completed. Note: This implementation is non-blocking and returns almost immediately.
        Parameters:
        messages - an array of messages to be hashed

The resulting hash value will be returned by the Message.getHash() method once the future (accessible from Message.getFuture()) has been completed. Note: This implementation is non-blocking and returns almost immediately.
        Parameters:
